    faqs: [
      { question: "Is GST included in business revenue?", answer: "No. For accounting and tax purposes, revenue is reported excluding GST (because GST collected is a liability payable to the government). Profit margins are calculated on ex-GST revenue." },
      { question: "How does ITC reduce my GST cost?", answer: "GST paid on purchases (ITC) is deducted from GST collected on sales. Net GST = Output GST − Input Tax Credit. If you collect ₹90K GST on sales and paid ₹60K GST on purchases, net GST payable is only ₹30K." },
      { question: "What is the income tax on business profit?", answer: "Sole proprietorship: taxed at individual slab rates (0-30%). Partnership: 30% flat. Company: 22% (new regime under Sec 115BAA, no MAT) or 25% (turnover ≤₹400Cr, regular). LLP: 30%. Choose business structure based on tax efficiency." },
      { question: "What expenses can I deduct from business profit?", answer: "Deductible: rent, salaries, utilities, depreciation, loan interest, marketing, professional fees, travel (business purpose), repairs and maintenance, insurance. Not deductible: personal expenses, penalties, TDS on non-compliant payments (40(a)(ia))." },
      { question: "What is presumptive taxation for small businesses?", answer: "Section 44AD: businesses with turnover ≤₹3Cr can declare 6% (digital receipts) or 8% (cash) of turnover as profit without maintaining detailed accounts. Section 44ADA: professionals with receipts ≤₹75L can declare 50% as profit." },
    ],
